His 2002 election ended 40 years of one-party rule since independence. However, his 2007 re-election sparked months of nationwide violence and led to 1 200 deaths. Kenyatta led the tributes, saying Kibaki had "led the charge to keep the ruling party accountable" and had "earned the abiding respect and affection" of this nation. Kenyatta declared a mourning period until Kibaki's burial, with the flying of flags at half-mast. Kibaki was noted for his liberal reforms, which revived Kenya's ailing economy, however he was accused of not doing enough to tackle rampant corruption. --BBC--